Rainfall in Coffs Harbour by month

Plan your trip to Coffs Harbour by taking into account the average rainfall totals by month.

In terms of precipitation, rainfall in Coffs Harbour ranges from 60.0 - 230.0 mm per month. March is typically the wettest month, when rainfall can reach 230.0 mm. September is typically the driest time to visit Coffs Harbour when rainfall is around 60.0 mm.

Temperature in Coffs Harbour by month

Plan your trip to Coffs Harbour by taking into account the average temperature totals by month.

If weather is an important factor for your trip to Coffs Harbour, use this chart to help with planning. For those seeking warmer temperatures, January is the ideal time of year to visit, when temperatures reach an average of 23.0 C. Travellers hoping to avoid the cold should look outside of July, when temperatures are typically at their lowest (around 12.0 C).

  • What does CFS mean?

    This is just an IATA (International Air Transport Association) code. IATA codes are used in aviation to identify and differentiate airports. That’s why a Coffs Harbour Airport flight would often be abbreviated as a CFS flight.

  • What airport do you fly into for flights to Coffs Harbour?

    Travellers will need to book flights to Coffs Harbour (CFS) if they wish to fly to Coffs Harbour. The Coffs Harbour airport is 3.0 km from the city centre.

  • Can I find cheaper flights to Coffs Harbour if I am willing to have stopovers?

    Yes, flights with stopovers are often cheaper than direct flights. Keep an eye out for flight deals to Coffs Harbour on Cheapflights that require 1 or 2 stops for potential cost savings.

    Yes. Those touching down at Coffs Harbour can take advantage of the car hire services offered upon their arrival.

  • Are there hotels close to Coffs Harbour?

    Yes. Coffs Harbour has hotels nearby for those requiring accommodations. Salt & Sea Park Beach 5 Min Walk To Beach is the closest property to Coffs Harbour (0.0 km away from Coffs Harbour).
